{
  "text": "The \"Instituto da Crian\u00e7a\" is a high-complexity pediatric hospital, affiliated with S\u00e3o Paulo State University. Children who are admitted to the PICU are usually chronically ill and treated by pediatric subspecialties from the institute itself. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Thus, one weakness of this study is it is not representative of the ventilatory practices of all Brazilian PICUs, but it may reflect the patterns of PICUs at other reference institutions in the country. Other weakness is that data extraction was performed around three years ago and practice could change in this time. Nevertheless, its major strength is to be the first Brazilian report of practice of mechanical ventilation in pediatric intensive care setting.",
